  "policy": {
    "privacy": "Only committed synthetic fixtures or explicitly licensed, provenance-tracked external fixtures may participate. Local clinical paths and PHI are forbidden.",
    "lossless": "Canonical stored samples must match exactly; reports identify the first differing sample, component, and frame.",
    "nearLossless": "Every reconstructed sample must remain within the explicitly encoded NEAR bound.",
    "lossy": "A case must declare its metric and rationale. No universal clinical threshold is inferred by this harness.",
    "metadata": "Transfer syntax, encapsulation, pixel description, frame order, and required DICOM geometry remain exact even for lossy pixels.",
    "gaps": "Missing licensed fixtures remain visible with a named owner and reason; they are never removed to make a report green."
